title: Test
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Capacity factor, with a total of 16 data points.
Overall Capacity factor has increased over the Year.

Capacity factor is roughly constant from 1975 to 1980, rapidly increasing from 1980 to 2000, roughly constant from 2000 to 2011, roughly increasing from 2011 to 2012, and lastly roughly constant from 2012 to 2018.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 1990 and 1995.
Max Capacity factor about 92.6 was recorded at Year 2018
Min Capacity factor about 55.9 was recorded at Year 1975
This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Capacity factor, with a total of 16 data points. The chart has 4 significant trends.
The longest trend is extremely increasing which exists from 1975 to 2010.
In a similar manner, the next significant trend is moderately constant which exists from 2015 to 2018.
Conversely, the next significant trend is extremely increasing which exists from 2012 to 2015.
Correspondingly, the next significant trend is slightly decreasing which exists from 2010 to 2012.
